## Snapshot Update Workflows

### Scenario 1: Visual Change (Intentional)

1. Run tests to see failures: `npm run test:storybook`
2. Review visual diffs
3. Update snapshots: `npm run test:storybook:update`
4. Verify tests pass
5. Update COMPONENT_TEST_MATRIX.md

### Scenario 2: Component Behavior Changed

1. Update play function to match new behavior
2. Run tests: `npm run test:storybook`
3. Update snapshots if needed
4. Verify all browsers: `npm run test:storybook:all`

### Scenario 3: Component Deleted

1. Detect orphaned story file (→ File 0d workflow)
2. Delete story file and snapshots
3. Update COMPONENT_TEST_MATRIX.md

---

## Maintenance Checklist

### After Component Changes

- [ ] Update play function if behavior changed
- [ ] Update snapshots if visuals changed
- [ ] Verify tests pass
- [ ] Update COMPONENT_TEST_MATRIX.md

### Before Release

- [ ] All play functions pass
- [ ] All unit tests pass
- [ ] Documentation up to date
- [ ] No orphaned test files

---

## Git Workflow

### Committing Test Changes

```bash
# New play functions
git commit -m "test: add play functions for modus-wc-button"

# Updated play functions
git commit -m "test: update modus-wc-button tests for new variant"

# Snapshot updates
git commit -m "test: update snapshots after design update"

# Fixed tests
git commit -m "fix: correct modus-wc-button test timing issue"
```

### PR Requirements

- [ ] All tests pass locally
- [ ] Play functions reviewed and correct
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] No console errors

